{"type":"message","id":"c6182114","parentId":"3fe0f217","timestamp":"2026-02-13T17:53:40.259Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"browser_1771005220251_151","name":"browser","arguments":{"targetId":"427D0DC0B650E856B9652AB209619E07","action":"snapshot","profile":"openclaw"},"thoughtSignature":"EjQKMgG+Pvb7SE2huQFLWrEssHDVY4NbYgTpijYryWi/1dKhDgrP4+FET2+aI8GZGqqDDfEH"},{"type":"text","text":""}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-3-flash-preview","usage":{"input":23052,"output":57,"cacheRead":16247,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23109,"cost":{"input":0.011526,"output":0.000171,"cacheRead":0.0008123500000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.012509349999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771005217662}}
{"type":"message","id":"2c581370","parentId":"c6182114","timestamp":"2026-02-13T17:53:40.633Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"browser_1771005220251_151","toolName":"browser","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- generic [ref=e3]:\n  - banner [ref=e4]:\n    - generic [ref=e5]:\n      - link \"Waxpeer\" [ref=e7] [cursor=pointer]:\n        - /url: /\n        - img [ref=e8]\n        - text:  Waxpeer\n      - button \"menu\" [ref=e13] [cursor=pointer]\n  - generic [ref=e16]:\n    - complementary:           \n    - main [ref=e17]:\n      - generic [ref=e18]:\n        - generic [ref=e19]:\n          - generic [ref=e20]: \n          - generic [ref=e21]:\n            - text: \"Note: Full response details are available in the\"\n            - link \"Swagger documentation\" [ref=e22] [cursor=pointer]:\n              - /url: //api.waxpeer.com/docs\n            - text: .\n        - generic [ref=e23]:\n          - button \"Introducing Socket IO \" [ref=e24] [cursor=pointer]:\n            - text: Introducing Socket IO\n            - generic [ref=e25]: \n          - heading \"WAXPEER API | BUY/SELL/TRADE Items via P2P system 2.2.9\" [level=1] [ref=e26]:\n            - text: WAXPEER API | BUY/SELL/TRADE Items via P2P system\n            - generic [ref=e27]: 2.2.9\n          - heading \"Connect CS:GO/Rust instant withdraws and deposits to your website using WAXPEER. Our customers can sell Steam items, and you can use the API to buy skins to any Steam trade url and get a delivery report. You can also find the trade websocket documentation here. Don't forget to open the schemas for more information about the parameters (status, message, price etc.).\" [level=2] [ref=e28]\n          - generic [ref=e29]:\n            - link \" Join our Telegram group to get instant support\" [ref=e30] [cursor=pointer]:\n              - /url: https://t.me/joinchat/F9z1d11ozKg2ZDMx\n              - generic [ref=e31]: \n              - generic [ref=e32]: Join our Telegram group to get instant support\n            - link \" Open Swagger model to test requests and get more info\" [ref=e33] [cursor=pointer]:\n              - /url: //api.waxpeer.com/docs\n              - generic [ref=e34]: \n              - generic [ref=e35]: Open Swagger model to test requests and get more info\n            - link \" Use NPM Module to interact with API\" [ref=e36] [cursor=pointer]:\n              - /url: //npmjs.com/package/waxpeer\n              - generic [ref=e37]: \n              - generic [ref=e38]: Use NPM Module to interact with API\n        - generic [ref=e39]:\n          - heading \"Updates\" [level=3] [ref=e40]\n          - list [ref=e41]:\n            - listitem [ref=e42]:\n              - generic [ref=e43]:\n                - paragraph [ref=e44]: New Payout Scheme\n                - list [ref=e45]:\n                  - listitem [ref=e46]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e47]: Funds from sales are credited 7 days after the item is delivered to the buyer.\n                  - listitem [ref=e48]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e49]: \"Until then, they remain in hold: visible on the trade page but unavailable for withdrawal.\"\n                  - listitem [ref=e50]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e51]: If the item is returned by the buyer (reason = \"Reversed by buyer\"), a 30% penalty is applied.\n            - listitem [ref=e52]:\n              - generic [ref=e53]:\n                - paragraph [ref=e54]: Trader API Updates\n                - list [ref=e55]:\n                  - listitem [ref=e56]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e57]: \"New fields added:\"\n                    - list [ref=e58]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e59]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e60]: is_released (boolean)\n                      - listitem [ref=e61]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e62]: release_date (timestamp)\n                    - paragraph\n                  - listitem [ref=e63]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e64]: \"If an item has status 4 (sent) and is_released=false:\"\n                    - list [ref=e65]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e66]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e67]: The buyer has already accepted the item\n                      - listitem [ref=e68]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e69]: The final status will be applied after release_date once the trade is rechecked\n                    - paragraph\n                  - listitem [ref=e70]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e71]: If the item is returned by the buyer (reason = \"Reversed by buyer\"), a 30% penalty is applied.\n            - listitem [ref=e72]:\n              - generic [ref=e73]:\n                - paragraph [ref=e74]: Updated Endpoints\n                - list [ref=e75]:\n                  - listitem [ref=e76]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e77]: /v1/check-many-project-id and /v1/check-many-steam\n                    - list [ref=e78]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e79]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e80]: Return is_released, release_date, and penalties (30% penalty if reason='Reversed by buyer').\n                    - paragraph\n                  - listitem [ref=e81]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e82]: /v1/my-history\n                    - list [ref=e83]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e84]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e85]: Includes new fields\n                      - listitem [ref=e86]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e87]: New filter hold_only (shows only deals with funds on hold)\n                    - paragraph\n                  - listitem [ref=e88]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e89]: /v1/user\n                    - list [ref=e90]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e91]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e92]: New field total_hold_amount (1000 = $1)\n                    - paragraph\n        - generic [ref=e93]:\n          - generic [ref=e95]: SocketIO\n          - generic [ref=e96]:\n            - generic [ref=e97]: Socket.IO is a JavaScript library that enables real-time, bidirectional communication between the server and the client. This guide will walk you through the steps to integrate waxpeer Socket.IO into your application.\n            - generic [ref=e98]:\n              - generic [ref=e101]: wss://waxpeer.com/socket.io/?EIO=4&transport=websocket\n              - list [ref=e103]:\n                - listitem [ref=e104]:\n                  - generic [ref=e105]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e106]: \"Authentication is done in 2 ways:\"\n                    - list [ref=e107]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e108]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e109]: Session based via cookies in headers\n                      - listitem [ref=e110]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e111]: Having waxpeer API in header as authorization\n                - listitem [ref=e112]:\n                  - generic [ref=e113]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e114]: \"After you can use the sub/subscribe and unsubscribe methods to listen for specific public events, such as:\"\n                    - list [ref=e115]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e116]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e117]: csgo,rust,tf2,dota2 (It will emit new,removed,update events per item)\n                      - listitem [ref=e118]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e119]: privat_sales or item_id of specific item.\n                      - listitem [ref=e120]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e121]: inspect\n                - listitem [ref=e122]:\n                  - generic [ref=e123]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e124]: User events currently supported\n                    - list [ref=e125]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e126]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e127]: payment\n                      - listitem [ref=e128]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e129]: notification\n                      - listitem [ref=e130]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e131]: change_user\n                      - listitem [ref=e132]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e133]: connection\n                      - listitem [ref=e134]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e135]: steamTrade\n                - listitem [ref=e136]:\n                  - generic [ref=e137]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e138]: Authorization must be in the header\n                    - list [ref=e139]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e140]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e141]: \"authorization: WAXPEER_KEY\"\n                      - listitem [ref=e142]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e143]: \"Cookie: _redis=s%3Ayour_session_cookie\"\n                - listitem [ref=e144]:\n                  - generic [ref=e145]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e146]: Subscribe/Unsubscribe\n                    - list [ref=e147]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e148]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e149]: \"42[\\\"subscribed\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"34574745489\\\"}]\"\n                      - listitem [ref=e150]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e151]: \"42[\\\"unsubscribed\\\",{\\\"name\\\":\\\"34574745489\\\"}]\"\n          - generic [ref=e152]:\n            - generic [ref=e153]: It will emit new, removed, update events per item for games like CS:GO, Rust, TF2, Dota 2.\n            - generic [ref=e154]:\n              - generic [ref=e156]:\n                - heading \"Object structure for game item events, detailing specific attributes of an item along with the event type.\" [level=5] [ref=e159]\n                - generic [ref=e160]:\n                  - code [ref=e162]: \"{ \\\"event\\\": \\\"string (new | removed | update)\\\", \\\"game\\\": \\\"string (csgo | rust | tf2 | dota2)\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"float\\\": \\\"number (optional, applicable to CS:GO items)\\\", \\\"price\\\": \\\"number\\\", \\\"item_id\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"paint_index\\\": \\\"number (optional, applicable to CS:GO items)\\\", \\\"selling\\\": \\\"boolean (optional)\\\", \\\"sticker_names\\\": \\\"array of strings (optional, applicable to CS:GO items)\\\" }\"\n                  - button \"\" [ref=e163] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - generic [ref=e164]: \n              - list [ref=e166]:\n                - listitem [ref=e167]:\n                  - generic [ref=e168]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e169]: You have to first send a subscribe event for the game you want to listen to.\n                    - list [ref=e170]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e171]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e172]: csgo\n                      - listitem [ref=e173]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e174]: rust\n                      - listitem [ref=e175]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e176]: tf2\n                      - listitem [ref=e177]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e178]: dota2\n            - generic [ref=e181]:\n              - generic [ref=e182]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e184]:\n                - code [ref=e186]: \"{ \\\"event\\\": \\\"update\\\", \\\"game\\\": \\\"csgo\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"AWP | Gungnir (Well-Worn)\\\", \\\"float\\\": 0.44339460134506226, \\\"price\\\": 7260000, \\\"item_id\\\": \\\"34822680618\\\", \\\"paint_index\\\": 756, \\\"sticker_names\\\": [ \\\"Sticker | keshandr (Foil) | Krakow 2017\\\" ] }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e187] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e188]: \n          - generic [ref=e189]:\n            - generic [ref=e190]: It will emit object key changes from User (wallet, kyc_status, no_p2p_until, failed_trades, failed_row, success_trades and etc.)\n            - generic [ref=e193]:\n              - heading \"Object structure for user changes\" [level=5] [ref=e196]\n              - generic [ref=e197]:\n                - code [ref=e199]: \"{ \\\"wallet\\\": \\\"number (optional)\\\", \\\"kyc_status\\\": \\\"string (optional)\\\", \\\"no_p2p_until\\\": \\\"string (ISO 8601 date-time format, optional)\\\", \\\"failed_trades\\\": \\\"number (optional)\\\", \\\"failed_row\\\": \\\"number (optional)\\\", \\\"success_trades\\\": \\\"number (optional)\\\" }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e200] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e201]: \n            - generic [ref=e204]:\n              - generic [ref=e205]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e207]:\n                - code [ref=e209]: \"{ \\\"wallet\\\": 10000, \\\"kyc_status\\\": \\\"requested\\\", \\\"no_p2p_until\\\": \\\"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\\\", \\\"failed_trades\\\": 2, \\\"failed_row\\\": 2, \\\"success_trades\\\": 5 }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e210] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e211]: \n          - generic [ref=e212]:\n            - generic [ref=e213]: Emits steam trade information to both buyer and seller, identical for both, for create or update operations.\n            - generic [ref=e216]:\n              - heading \"Structure for steam trade events, indicating trade updates or creations.\" [level=5] [ref=e219]\n              - generic [ref=e220]:\n                - code [ref=e222]:\n                  - text: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"data\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"costum_id\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"creator\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"boxed\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"send_until\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"last_updated\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"done\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e223]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"now\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"user\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"can_p2p\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e224]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"kyc_status\\\": \\\"string\\\" }, \\\"merchant\\\": { \\\"merchant\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"currency_value\\\": 0, \\\"currency_icon\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"successlink\\\": \\\"string\\\" }, \\\"seller\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"can_p2p\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e225]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"kyc_status\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"shop\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"auto\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e226]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \"}, \\\"for\\\": { \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"kyc_status\\\": \\\"string\\\" }, \\\"items\\\": [ { \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"merchant\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"trade_id\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"sent_time\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"inspect_item\\\": { \\\"floatvalue\\\": 0, \\\"rarity_name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"stickers\\\": [ { \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"wear\\\": 0, \\\"sticker_price\\\": { \\\"img\\\": \\\"string\\\" } } ] }, \\\"steam_prices\\\": { \\\"rarity_color\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"collection\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"collection_icon\\\": \\\"string\\\" } } ] } }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e227] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e228]: \n            - generic [ref=e231]:\n              - generic [ref=e232]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e234]:\n                - code [ref=e236]:\n                  - text: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"update\\\", \\\"data\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"10546645\\\", \\\"stage\\\": 1, \\\"send_until\\\": \\\"2024-02-05T22:21:31.645Z\\\", \\\"last_updated\\\": \\\"2024-02-05T22:16:10.709Z\\\", \\\"done\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e237]: \"false\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"boxed\\\": \\\"2024-02-05T22:15:36.645Z\\\", \\\"costum_id\\\": \\\"710a2b8c-3c24-47e8-9b8b-028b177ff0ed\\\", \\\"creator\\\": \\\"seller\\\", \\\"now\\\": \\\"2024-02-05T22:16:10.712Z\\\", \\\"merchant\\\": { \\\"merchant\\\": \\\"skinpeer\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"1605372312364-wax-logo.jpg\\\", \\\"currency_value\\\": 1, \\\"currency_icon\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e238]: \"null\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"successlink\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e239]: \"null\"\n                  - text: \"}, \\\"user\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"dadf0f33-3563-441a-9ae0-73c0d1b1954c\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"ITY\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"https://avatars.steamstatic.com/cb2e23107e1b8a23c38e89ed4b296855d3f0a523_medium.jpg\\\", \\\"can_p2p\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e240]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"kyc_status\\\": \\\"approved\\\" }, \\\"seller\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"1ee21a71-b222-4fa0-bc74-7b69e929f59d\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"pashkin\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"https://avatars.akamai.steamstatic.com/29108b7865c3aa9b802b89ade6874db85444f177_medium.jpg\\\", \\\"can_p2p\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e241]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"kyc_status\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e242]: \"null\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"shop\\\": \\\"1ee21a71-b222-4fa0-bc74-7b69e929f59d\\\", \\\"auto\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e243]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"success_trades\\\": 17, \\\"failed_trades\\\": 1 }, \\\"for\\\": { \\\"name\\\": \\\"ITY\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"https://avatars.steamstatic.com/cb2e23107e1b8a23c38e89ed4b296855d3f0a523_medium.jpg\\\", \\\"kyc_status\\\": \\\"approved\\\", \\\"steam_joined\\\": 1476828448, \\\"steam_level\\\": 151 }, \\\"items\\\": [ { \\\"id\\\": 11491794, \\\"price\\\": 2951, \\\"name\\\": \\\"StatTrak™ AK-47 | Elite Build (Field-Tested)\\\", \\\"status\\\": 0, \\\"merchant\\\": \\\"skinpeer\\\", \\\"item_id\\\": 35561226317, \\\"trade_id\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e244]: \"null\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://steamcommunity-a.akamaihd.net/economy/image/class/730/5701259026/200fx125f\\\", \\\"sent_time\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e245]: \"null\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"inspect_item\\\": { \\\"floatvalue\\\": 0.2730073928833008, \\\"rarity_name\\\": \\\"Mil-Spec Grade\\\", \\\"stickers\\\": [ { \\\"name\\\": \\\"Sticker | Ninjas in Pyjamas | Cologne 2015\\\", \\\"slot\\\": 3, \\\"wear\\\": 0, \\\"sticker_price\\\": { \\\"average\\\": 2680, \\\"img\\\": \\\"https://steamcommunity-a.akamaihd.net/economy/image/-9a81dlWLwJ2UUGcVs_nsVtzdOEdtWwKGZZLQHTxDZ7I56KU0Zwwo4NUX4oFJZEHLbXQ9QVcJY8gulReQ0DfQOqohZ-CBhJ6LApdt6msJRd52fLFcC4MuoTukoXekvGiZbnTkDpUvpRyiO3H8Irz3A3h_UVqY2Dyco_HcgdrNEaQpAaDo1ajzA\\\" } }, { \\\"name\\\": \\\"Sticker | friberg | Cologne 2015\\\", \\\"slot\\\": 2, \\\"wear\\\": 0, \\\"sticker_price\\\": { \\\"average\\\": 1500, \\\"img\\\": \\\"-9a81dlWLwJ2UUGcVs_nsVtzdOEdtWwKGZZLQHTxDZ7I56KU0Zwwo4NUX4oFJZEHLbXQ9QVcJY8gulReQ0DfQOqohZ-CBhJnLANosKisKQJy1MzEcC9F6ZLlloPbzvajZu6Azm0FvpJ32LzFoIin3FGy-UdkN2qldo-WdlU6ZFnU5BHglk8vJLEl\\\" } }, { \\\"name\\\": \\\"Sticker | f0rest | Cologne 2015\\\", \\\"slot\\\": 1, \\\"wear\\\": 0, \\\"sticker_price\\\": { \\\"average\\\": 1730, \\\"img\\\": \\\"-9a81dlWLwJ2UUGcVs_nsVtzdOEdtWwKGZZLQHTxDZ7I56KU0Zwwo4NUX4oFJZEHLbXQ9QVcJY8gulReQ0DfQOqohZ-CBhJnLANosLW3LhR07P_JYzpHot7vwtaPzvOlMe-AkDNV7pRyi-vEpt-m3AWyr0VuZmmhJYSTdg45NFnOug_pdZ8zr4A\\\" } }, { \\\"name\\\": \\\"Sticker | GeT_RiGhT | Cologne 2015\\\", \\\"slot\\\": 0, \\\"wear\\\": 0, \\\"sticker_price\\\": { \\\"average\\\": 2110, \\\"img\\\": \\\"-9a81dlWLwJ2UUGcVs_nsVtzdOEdtWwKGZZLQHTxDZ7I56KU0Zwwo4NUX4oFJZEHLbXQ9QVcJY8gulReQ0DfQOqohZ-CBhJnLANosb-xOQ5n2-f3fTxQ69n4xIKJk_WnYO3XlGhX7sZ33ryZotimjATjqkU4ZmihLI6TdVA9NV_V_E_-n7nIWggTQg\\\" } } ] }, \\\"steam_prices\\\": { \\\"rarity_color\\\": \\\"#EB4B4B\\\", \\\"game_id\\\": 730, \\\"collection\\\": \\\"The Cobblestone Collection\\\", \\\"collection_icon\\\": \\\"https://cdn.csmarketcap.com/icons/the-cobblestone-collection.png\\\" } } ] } }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e246] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e247]: \n          - generic [ref=e248]:\n            - generic [ref=e249]: Emits a full connection object if there is a create, update, or delete operation.\n            - generic [ref=e252]:\n              - heading \"Structure for connection events. The 'data' field is present for create and update operations, and 'previous_data' is provided for delete operations.\" [level=5] [ref=e255]\n              - generic [ref=e256]:\n                - code [ref=e258]: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"data\\\": {}, \\\"previous_data\\\": {} }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e259] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e260]: \n            - generic [ref=e263]:\n              - generic [ref=e264]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e266]:\n                - code [ref=e268]:\n                  - text: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"delete\\\", \\\"data\\\": \\\"null\\\", \\\"previous_data\\\": { \\\"id\\\": 4, \\\"username\\\": \\\"®Suspect4you®\\\", \\\"user\\\": \\\"2b4fd250-f1528-4307-904e-c86d7e7c0f65\\\", \\\"email\\\": \\\"asdad@hotmail.com\\\", \\\"avatar\\\": \\\"https://cdn.discordapp.com/avatars/374121399750492160/8d68bf6a22d3279341f6f51ee2c72509.png\\\", \\\"oauth\\\": \\\"discord\\\", \\\"oauth_id\\\": \\\"123\\\", \\\"discriminator\\\": \\\"31270\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2019-09-17T12:25:22.051749-04:00\\\", \\\"bot\\\": \\\"bot1\\\", \\\"main\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e269]: \"false\"\n                  - text: \"} }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e270] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e271]: \n          - generic [ref=e272]:\n            - generic [ref=e273]: Emits notification events, including updates or creation of notifications, to inform users about specific actions like sending items, trade updates, or other related activities.\n            - generic [ref=e276]:\n              - heading \"Object structure for notification events, detailing the notification attributes and the action that triggered the notification.\" [level=5] [ref=e279]\n              - generic [ref=e280]:\n                - code [ref=e282]: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"string (update | create)\\\", \\\"data\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"number\\\", \\\"user\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"link\\\": \\\"string (optional)\\\", \\\"action\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"string (optional)\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"parameter\\\": \\\"string (optional)\\\", \\\"read\\\": \\\"boolean\\\", \\\"identification\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"created\\\": \\\"string (ISO 8601 date-time format)\\\", \\\"updated\\\": \\\"string (ISO 8601 date-time format, optional)\\\" } }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e283] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e284]: \n            - generic [ref=e287]:\n              - generic [ref=e288]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e290]:\n                - code [ref=e292]:\n                  - text: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"update\\\", \\\"data\\\": { \\\"id\\\": 19240228, \\\"user\\\": \\\"dadf0f33-3563-441a-9ae0-73c0d1b1954c\\\", \\\"link\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e293]: \"null\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"action\\\": \\\"sending_steam\\\", \\\"image\\\": \\\"https://steamcommunity-a.akamaihd.net/economy/image/class/730/4302203073/200fx125f\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"Sticker | Heroic | 2020 RMR\\\", \\\"parameter\\\": \\\"canceled\\\", \\\"read\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e294]: \"true\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"identification\\\": \\\"10375241dadf0f33-3563-441a-9ae0-73c0d1b1954c25707995376\\\", \\\"created\\\": \\\"2024-01-18T09:15:33.330Z\\\", \\\"updated\\\": \\\"2024-01-19T05:29:12.758Z\\\" } }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e295] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e296]: \n          - generic [ref=e297]:\n            - generic [ref=e298]: Emits payment events, detailing updates or creation of payment transactions, to track the status and direction of payments.\n            - generic [ref=e301]:\n              - heading \"Object structure for payment events, providing details on the payment status, transaction ID, and whether the payment was incoming or outgoing.\" [level=5] [ref=e304]\n              - generic [ref=e305]:\n                - code [ref=e307]: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"string (update | create)\\\", \\\"data\\\": { \\\"id\\\": \\\"number\\\", \\\"status\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"transaction_id\\\": \\\"string (optional)\\\", \\\"updated\\\": \\\"string (ISO 8601 date-time format)\\\", \\\"direction\\\": \\\"string (in | out)\\\" } }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e308] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e309]: \n            - generic [ref=e312]:\n              - generic [ref=e313]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e315]:\n                - code [ref=e317]:\n                  - text: \"{ \\\"type\\\": \\\"update\\\", \\\"data\\\": { \\\"id\\\": 727016, \\\"status\\\": \\\"completed\\\", \\\"transaction_id\\\":\"\n                  - generic [ref=e318]: \"null\"\n                  - text: \", \\\"updated\\\": \\\"2023-12-17T23:05:11.991545-05:00\\\", \\\"direction\\\": \\\"out\\\" } }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e319] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e320]: \n        - generic [ref=e321]:\n          - generic [ref=e323]: Websocket\n          - generic [ref=e324]:\n            - generic [ref=e325]: Breaking changes due to Steam API update\n            - generic [ref=e326]:\n              - paragraph [ref=e330]: \"Now in order to go online and sell items safely you need to implement the following logic:\"\n              - list [ref=e332]:\n                - listitem [ref=e333]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e335]: Make sure that you have enabled the collection of user data on the website under the \"Sell items\" tab (by default it is enabled).\n                - listitem [ref=e336]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e338]:\n                    - text: Going online now requires a valid Steam access token because the API key functionality has been limited. You need to\n                    - link \"send it\" [ref=e339] [cursor=pointer]:\n                      - /url: https://docs.waxpeer.com/?method=v1-user-steam-token-post\n                    - text: once an hour or immediately after an refresh (the token is active only 24 hours after refreshing in Steam), otherwise it will expire and all your items will be disabled from sale, and active trades will be considered stalled and may be canceled\n                - listitem [ref=e340]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e342]: We categorically recommend not to make a mobile confirmation for a created trade until you send its trade id using the callback method.\n                - listitem [ref=e343]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e345]: Online may be delayed until the access token is verified or a valid token is received. Therefore, please note that in the trade socket there is a new user_change event, in which can_p2p indicates whether you are online or not when it is changed by p2p controller.\n                - listitem [ref=e346]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e348]:\n                    - text: If you do not want to use\n                    - link \"npm package\" [ref=e349] [cursor=pointer]:\n                      - /url: https://www.npmjs.com/package/waxpeer\n                    - text: \", but will be implementing your own trade socket connection, make sure you specify the source parameter on the authentification event (auth) without which the account will not be able to get online (example: \\\"source\\\": \\\"myAwesomeProject\\\").\"\n              - generic [ref=e350]:\n                - paragraph [ref=e353]:\n                  - text: We categorically recommend not to make a mobile confirmation for a created trade until you send its trade id using the\n                  - link \"callback\" [ref=e354] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - /url: https://docs.waxpeer.com/?method=v1-steam-trade-post\n                  - text: .\n                - paragraph [ref=e357]: Online may be delayed until the access token is verified or a valid token is received. Therefore, please note that in the trade socket there is a new user_change event, in which can_p2p indicates whether you are online or not when it is changed by p2p controller.\n                - paragraph [ref=e360]: \"If you do not want to use this package, but will be implementing your own trade socket connection, make sure you specify the source parameter on the authentification event (auth) without which the account will not be able to get online (example: 'source': 'myAwesomeProject').\"\n                - paragraph [ref=e363]:\n                  - text: You can see an example of the implementation steps\n                  - link \"here\" [ref=e364] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - /url: https://www.npmjs.com/package/waxpeer#initialization-with-the-new-requirements\n          - generic [ref=e365]:\n            - generic [ref=e366]: How to set up trade websocket\n            - generic [ref=e367]:\n              - generic [ref=e370]: wss://wssex.waxpeer.com\n              - list [ref=e372]:\n                - listitem [ref=e373]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e375]: Connect to websocket via any websocket library. Such as WS, Socket.IO client for Node.js\n                - listitem [ref=e376]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e378]: Send a ping command once per 25 seconds to keep the connection alive\n                - listitem [ref=e379]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e381]: Send your authentication object command to let our system recognize you\n                - listitem [ref=e382]:\n                  - generic [ref=e383]:\n                    - paragraph [ref=e384]: \"Be ready to react to the following object name events:\"\n                    - list [ref=e385]:\n                      - listitem [ref=e386]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e387]: send-trade (create trade)\n                      - listitem [ref=e388]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e389]: cancelTrade (cancel trade)\n                      - listitem [ref=e390]:\n                        - paragraph [ref=e391]: accept_withdraw (accept incoming trade)\n                - listitem [ref=e392]:\n                  - paragraph [ref=e394]: Don’t forget to confirm trade on mobile\n              - paragraph [ref=e396]: We recommend sending the trade only once\n          - generic [ref=e397]:\n            - generic [ref=e398]: Authentification\n            - generic [ref=e399]:\n              - paragraph [ref=e403]: You can now go online and sell from limited Steam accounts (Except Rust game). One from STEAM_API, WAX_API, ACCESS_TOKEN is required!\n              - generic [ref=e404]:\n                - heading \"Object parameters\" [level=5] [ref=e407]\n                - table [ref=e408]:\n                  - rowgroup [ref=e409]:\n                    - row \"Parameter Type Description\" [ref=e410]:\n                      - columnheader \"Parameter\" [ref=e411]:\n                        - generic [ref=e412]: Parameter\n                      - columnheader \"Type\" [ref=e413]:\n                        - generic [ref=e414]: Type\n                      - columnheader \"Description\" [ref=e415]:\n                        - generic [ref=e416]: Description\n                  - rowgroup [ref=e417]:\n                    - row \"source string your project name\" [ref=e418]:\n                      - cell \"source\" [ref=e419]:\n                        - generic [ref=e420]: source\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e421]:\n                        - generic [ref=e422]: string\n                      - cell \"your project name\" [ref=e423]:\n                        - generic [ref=e424]: your project name\n                    - row \"name string always “auth”\" [ref=e425]:\n                      - cell \"name\" [ref=e426]:\n                        - generic [ref=e427]: name\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e428]:\n                        - generic [ref=e429]: string\n                      - cell \"always “auth”\" [ref=e430]:\n                        - generic [ref=e431]: always “auth”\n                    - row \"steamid string steamid64\" [ref=e432]:\n                      - cell \"steamid\" [ref=e433]:\n                        - generic [ref=e434]: steamid\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e435]:\n                        - generic [ref=e436]: string\n                      - cell \"steamid64\" [ref=e437]:\n                        - generic [ref=e438]: steamid64\n                    - row \"apiKey string OPTIONAL. API key of your Steam account\" [ref=e439]:\n                      - cell \"apiKey\" [ref=e440]:\n                        - generic [ref=e441]: apiKey\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e442]:\n                        - generic [ref=e443]: string\n                      - cell \"OPTIONAL. API key of your Steam account\" [ref=e444]:\n                        - generic [ref=e445]: OPTIONAL. API key of your Steam account\n                    - row \"waxAPI string OPTIONAL. API key of your Waxpeer account\" [ref=e446]:\n                      - cell \"waxAPI\" [ref=e447]:\n                        - generic [ref=e448]: waxAPI\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e449]:\n                        - generic [ref=e450]: string\n                      - cell \"OPTIONAL. API key of your Waxpeer account\" [ref=e451]:\n                        - generic [ref=e452]: OPTIONAL. API key of your Waxpeer account\n                    - row \"accessToken string OPTIONAL. Access token of your Steam account (NOT encoded)\" [ref=e453]:\n                      - cell \"accessToken\" [ref=e454]:\n                        - generic [ref=e455]: accessToken\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e456]:\n                        - generic [ref=e457]: string\n                      - cell \"OPTIONAL. Access token of your Steam account (NOT encoded)\" [ref=e458]:\n                        - generic [ref=e459]: OPTIONAL. Access token of your Steam account (NOT encoded)\n                    - row \"tradeurl string your tradelink\" [ref=e460]:\n                      - cell \"tradeurl\" [ref=e461]:\n                        - generic [ref=e462]: tradeurl\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e463]:\n                        - generic [ref=e464]: string\n                      - cell \"your tradelink\" [ref=e465]:\n                        - generic [ref=e466]: your tradelink\n              - generic [ref=e467]:\n                - heading \"Object structure\" [level=5] [ref=e470]\n                - generic [ref=e471]:\n                  - code [ref=e473]: \"{ \\\"source\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"steamid\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"apiKey\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"waxAPI\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"accessToken\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"tradeurl\\\": \\\"string\\\" }\"\n                  - button \"\" [ref=e474] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - generic [ref=e475]: \n            - generic [ref=e478]:\n              - generic [ref=e479]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e481]:\n                - code [ref=e483]: \"{ \\\"source\\\": \\\"myAwesomeProject\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"auth\\\", \\\"steamid\\\": \\\"76561199059254XXX\\\", \\\"apiKey\\\": \\\"54###A171A5C7B08CA287A###228C029\\\", \\\"waxApi\\\": \\\"####124b4bd3847e33331f0e49194b9c798f613d5e732d17c4f5823f7f9c6a##\\\", \\\"accessToken\\\": \\\"eyAidHlwIjogIkpXVCIsICJhbGciOiAiRWREU0EiIH0.eyAiaXfsd23123123.2B9wKjf2323-S3i3ctdCg\\\", \\\"tradeurl\\\": \\\"https://steamcommunity.com/tradeoffer/new/?partner=1234567890&token=asd1-5zF\\\" }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e484] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e485]: \n          - generic [ref=e486]:\n            - generic [ref=e487]: Ping\n            - generic [ref=e488]:\n              - paragraph [ref=e492]: Send a ping command once per 25 seconds to keep the connection alive\n              - generic [ref=e493]:\n                - heading \"Object parameters\" [level=5] [ref=e496]\n                - table [ref=e497]:\n                  - rowgroup [ref=e498]:\n                    - row \"Parameter Type Description\" [ref=e499]:\n                      - columnheader \"Parameter\" [ref=e500]:\n                        - generic [ref=e501]: Parameter\n                      - columnheader \"Type\" [ref=e502]:\n                        - generic [ref=e503]: Type\n                      - columnheader \"Description\" [ref=e504]:\n                        - generic [ref=e505]: Description\n                  - rowgroup [ref=e506]:\n                    - row \"name string always “ping”\" [ref=e507]:\n                      - cell \"name\" [ref=e508]:\n                        - generic [ref=e509]: name\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e510]:\n                        - generic [ref=e511]: string\n                      - cell \"always “ping”\" [ref=e512]:\n                        - generic [ref=e513]: always “ping”\n              - generic [ref=e514]:\n                - heading \"Object structure\" [level=5] [ref=e517]\n                - generic [ref=e518]:\n                  - code [ref=e520]: \"{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\" }\"\n                  - button \"\" [ref=e521] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - generic [ref=e522]: \n            - generic [ref=e525]:\n              - generic [ref=e526]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e528]:\n                - code [ref=e530]: \"{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"ping\\\" }\"\n                - button \"\" [ref=e531] [cursor=pointer]:\n                  - generic [ref=e532]: \n          - generic [ref=e533]:\n            - generic [ref=e534]: Pong\n            - generic [ref=e535]:\n              - generic [ref=e536]:\n                - generic [ref=e538]: pong\n                - paragraph [ref=e541]: Event notifying that a ping command has been received\n              - generic [ref=e542]:\n                - heading \"Event parameters\" [level=5] [ref=e545]\n                - table [ref=e546]:\n                  - rowgroup [ref=e547]:\n                    - row \"Parameter Type Description\" [ref=e548]:\n                      - columnheader \"Parameter\" [ref=e549]:\n                        - generic [ref=e550]: Parameter\n                      - columnheader \"Type\" [ref=e551]:\n                        - generic [ref=e552]: Type\n                      - columnheader \"Description\" [ref=e553]:\n                        - generic [ref=e554]: Description\n                  - rowgroup [ref=e555]:\n                    - row \"name string always “pong”\" [ref=e556]:\n                      - cell \"name\" [ref=e557]:\n                        - generic [ref=e558]: name\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e559]:\n                        - generic [ref=e560]: string\n                      - cell \"always “pong”\" [ref=e561]:\n                        - generic [ref=e562]: always “pong”\n                    - row \"msg string always “1”\" [ref=e563]:\n                      - cell \"msg\" [ref=e564]:\n                        - generic [ref=e565]: msg\n                      - cell \"string\" [ref=e566]:\n                        - generic [ref=e567]: string\n                      - cell \"always “1”\" [ref=e568]:\n                        - generic [ref=e569]: always “1”\n              - generic [ref=e570]:\n                - heading \"Event structure\" [level=5] [ref=e573]\n                - generic [ref=e574]:\n                  - code [ref=e576]: \"{ \\\"name\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"data\\\": { \\\"msg\\\": \\\"string\\\" } }\"\n                  - button \"\" [ref=e577] [cursor=pointer]:\n                    - generic [ref=e578]: \n            - generic [ref=e581]:\n              - generic [ref=e582]: Example\n              - generic [ref=e584]:\n   